sentences: Philip Fuemana (6 January 1964 – 28 February 2005) was a New Zealand musician.
Fuemana died of a heart attack at his Auckland home in 2005.
The Otara Millionaire's Club was originally formed in 1993 by Phil Fuemana.
The OMC reached worldwide fame in 1995 with the single "How Bizarre", from the debut album of the same name.
